# module example

Renders few-shot examples. Examples trigger pattern replication — the model matches output style to what it sees rather than what it infers from description. The instruction to replicate "exactly" reduces creative drift.

# entity Output

```markdown
## [FEW-SHOT SYNTAX EXAMPLES{{#name}}: {{name}}{{/name}}]

The following example demonstrates the required implementation pattern. Replicate this structure, naming conventions, and style exactly:

{{body}}
```

# rule

- name is optional. {{#name}}: {{name}}{{/name}} is a conditional block — included only when name is non-empty.
- When name is absent the header is: `## [FEW-SHOT SYNTAX EXAMPLES]`
- Fenced code blocks within the body must be preserved exactly, including language tags and indentation.
- Multiple example blocks render as separate sections. The compiler does not merge them — order and separation between examples is intentional for few-shot clarity.
